1 SECTION 3. IC 22-9.5-2-14 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
2 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
3 1, 2026]: Sec. 14. "Veteran" has the meaning set forth in
4 IC 22-9-1-3.
5 SECTION 4. IC 22-9.5-5-1 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
6 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 1. (a) A person may not
7 refuse to sell or to rent after the making of a bona fide offer, refuse to
8 negotiate for the sale or rental of, or otherwise make unavailable or
9 deny a dwelling to any person because of race, color, religion, sex,
10 familial status, disability, or national origin, source of income, active
11 duty status, or veteran status.
12 (b) A person may not discriminate against any person in the terms,
13 conditions, or privileges of sale or rental of a dwelling, or in providing
14 services or facilities in connection with the sale or rental of a dwelling,
15 because of race, color, religion, sex, familial status, disability, or
16 national origin, source of income, active duty status, or veteran
17 status.
18 (c) This section does not prohibit discrimination against a person
19 because the person has been convicted under federal law or the law of
20 any state of the illegal manufacture or distribution of a controlled
21 substance.
22 SECTION 5. IC 22-9.5-5-2 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
23 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 2. A person may not
24 make, print, or publish or cause to be made, printed, or published any
25 notice, statement, or advertisement with respect to the sale or rental of
26 a dwelling that indicates any preference, limitation, or discrimination
27 based on race, color, religion, sex, disability, familial status, or national
28 origin, source of income, active duty status, or veteran status, or an
29 intention to make such a preference, limitation, or discrimination.
30 SECTION 6. IC 22-9.5-5-3 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
31 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 3. A person may not
32 represent to any person because of race, color, religion, sex, disability,
33 familial status, or national origin, source of income, active duty
34 status, or veteran status that a dwelling is not available for inspection
35 for sale or rental when the dwelling is available for inspection.
36 SECTION 7. IC 22-9.5-5-4 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
37 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 4. A person may not,
38 for profit, induce or attempt to induce a person to sell or rent a dwelling
39 by representations regarding the entry or prospective entry into a
40 neighborhood of a person of a particular race, color, religion, sex,
41 disability, familial status, or national origin, source of income, active
42 duty status, or veteran status.
